I... got accepted... into grad school.

82
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:40,340
Oh... congratulations.

83
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:43,570
Thank you.

84
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:48,090
But I'm not going to register for classes.

85
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:06,770
Song Ah. This...

86
00:14:21,780 --> 00:14:25,360
   

87
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:29,320
I'm not trying to pressure you.

88
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:33,290
Yes. I know.

89
00:14:35,590 --> 00:14:40,700
I decided not to compete in the Tchaikovsky Competition.

90
00:14:44,340 --> 00:14:49,540
I've learned a lot... thanks to you.

91
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:56,930
I decided to try playing my music freely.

92
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,880
Thank you.

93
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:53,600
Hello, Assistant Manager.

94
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:56,750
Oh, Song Ah! You're here.

95
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:05,790
Umm... you used to play an instrument really well, right?

96
00:16:05,790 --> 00:16:10,050
You even got first place in the Daehan Ilbo Competition.

97
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:14,590
Why did you choose to do this work?

98
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:18,580
In my case,

99
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:21,410
rather than struggling in the practice room by myself,

100
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:25,770
I preferred making trouble with people outside the practice room.

101
00:16:25,770 --> 00:16:28,830
As they say nowadays, I'm an "insider."

102
00:16:32,460 --> 00:16:34,520
But Song Ah,

103
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:39,650
don't be so quick to give up practicing music.

104
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:43,280
Even if you haven't practiced music for long compared to the other guys,

105
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:46,570
you mustn't cut it off so suddenly.

106
00:16:47,890 --> 00:16:51,750
Decrease your practice time slowly, bit by bit.

107
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:54,970
Take your time in saying goodbye.

108
00:16:58,410 --> 00:17:03,050
Oh, Song Ah! Sorry! Traffic was murder.

109
00:17:03,050 --> 00:17:07,560
All of us want to work with you.

110
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:12,030
Except, as I mentioned earlier, we don't have many part-time positions,

111
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:16,000
and I'm not certain when we'll have

112
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,270
full-time positions again.

113
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:23,850
Since we have these real-life issues, will you think carefully about this before getting back to me?

114
00:17:24,570 --> 00:17:29,290
But do you think I'd do a good job?

115
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:37,180
Song Ah. On the day of Cho Soo Han's performance,

116
00:17:37,180 --> 00:17:40,920
when you didn't hesitate to give her your shoes,

117
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:46,460
and when you realized since she was just about to perform, you bore her mean insults,

118
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:51,220
you did all that because you thought of the musician first, right?

119
00:17:52,350 --> 00:17:55,700
The reason why I'm inviting you to work with me

120
00:17:55,700 --> 00:18:01,130
is because you always consider others first, take care of them, and look after them.

121
00:18:01,130 --> 00:18:05,030
I think that makes you a good fit for this job.

122
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:13,030
But isn't that something anyone could do?

123
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:15,350
- For me— 
 - No.

124
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:22,260
If it were something anyone could do... wouldn't everyone do it?

125
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:31,610
In musical terms, they call it a "crescendo."

126
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:34,960
It means "to increase in intensity," right?

127
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,790
Yes.

128
00:18:36,790 --> 00:18:40,670
If we take "to increase in intensity" and reverse it,

129
00:18:40,670 --> 00:18:44,040
it means this place is where it's the quietest.

130
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:49,460
It's because this place is the quietest, that later it can grow in intensity.

131
00:18:54,310 --> 00:18:59,530
15 years ago, when I was interviewed to work at this foundation,

132
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:05,870
I had given up on figure skating, and both my self-confidence and self-esteem hit rock bottom.

133
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:08,810
Chairman Na said this to me,

134
00:19:09,930 --> 00:19:14,010
"If we took your smallest moment, and reworded it...

135
00:19:14,010 --> 00:19:18,150
wouldn't it be the beginning of your crescendo?"

136
00:19:23,550 --> 00:19:28,920
Would you carefully consider today's offer and get back to me?

137
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:34,100
Okay. I'll do that.

138
00:19:35,410 --> 00:19:37,480
None of today's songs have accompaniments.

139
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:38,940
You're right.

140
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:42,490
Wow, playing by yourself with no accompanist for 90 minutes must be brutal, right?

141
00:19:42,490 --> 00:19:43,590
Yeah.

142
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:46,490
But is this all there is?

143
00:19:46,490 --> 00:19:49,640
   

144
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:52,030
   

145
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:54,270
   

146
00:21:43,490 --> 00:21:45,140
Yes?

147
00:22:01,230 --> 00:22:06,060
I really enjoyed your performance today.

148
00:22:06,060 --> 00:22:11,750
Thank you. I didn't know you would come.

149
00:22:12,950 --> 00:22:15,220
I wanted to come.

150
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:19,920
During the master class last time...

151
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:22,370
 How do I... 

152
00:22:22,370 --> 00:22:26,420
 gain confidence? 

153
00:22:27,430 --> 00:22:29,890
 That's a tough question. 

154
00:22:32,380 --> 00:22:36,900
 If you find the answer, could you share it with me too? 

155
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:41,070
Hearing your performance today,

156
00:22:41,070 --> 00:22:46,100
I think you've found the answer already.

157
00:22:52,010 --> 00:22:55,860
Thank you, Song Ah.

158
00:22:58,730 --> 00:23:01,810
Today, thanks to you,

159
00:23:01,810 --> 00:23:08,470
I thought of why I loved the violin again.

160
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:11,540
Because the violin...

161
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:16,880
is an instrument you play by standing on both your feet.

162
00:23:18,130 --> 00:23:20,630
It's an instrument that required me

163
00:23:20,630 --> 00:23:25,010
to play it while maintaining my stance without wavering.

164
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:30,150
I think that's what I liked about it.

165
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:39,910
Unni!

166
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:46,290
Our chamber orchestra is holding a foundation concert.

167
00:23:46,290 --> 00:23:49,140
Please come if you have time.

168
00:23:49,710 --> 00:23:51,360
Is that so?

169
00:23:53,470 --> 00:23:55,830
By the way,

170
00:23:57,110 --> 00:24:01,250
I heard the student who worked for you quit.

171
00:24:04,060 --> 00:24:07,740
Yes, I fired her.

172
00:24:08,540 --> 00:24:11,430
She was polite and seemed to be a good worker.

173
00:24:11,430 --> 00:24:17,620
That's true. Not everyone is popular with people.

174
00:24:19,010 --> 00:24:21,430
I said I fired her.

175
00:24:21,430 --> 00:24:23,650
Oh, really?

176
00:24:27,890 --> 00:24:31,800
 Song Ah, have you been well? 

177
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:34,740
   

178
00:24:46,130 --> 00:24:49,280
Why are you barely eating? Do you not have an appetite?

179
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:51,360
No, that's not it.

180
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:55,820
When is your boyfriend's graduation performance?

181
00:24:55,820 --> 00:24:57,720
What?

182
00:24:57,720 --> 00:25:00,700
Your boyfriend is going to have a graduation performance, isn't he?

183
00:25:02,330 --> 00:25:08,820
Mom, we broke up.

184
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,000
Why?

185
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:18,450
It... just ended up that way.

186
00:25:18,450 --> 00:25:20,670
How could it have "just" happened?

187
00:25:22,390 --> 00:25:24,380
You're right.

188
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:27,550
He was also your accompanist for your graduation performance, wasn't he?

189
00:25:29,570 --> 00:25:32,210
We were already broken up then.

190
00:25:32,210 --> 00:25:38,650
He just did it for me as a friend.

191
00:25:42,290 --> 00:25:44,390
I was really grateful to him then.

192
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:53,290
Though I didn't particularly support you studying music,

193
00:25:53,290 --> 00:25:57,830
the day of your graduation performance, I actually felt a bit uneasy.

194
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:01,530
It was something you wanted to do so badly,

195
00:26:02,490 --> 00:26:06,160
and I couldn't do it in place of you.

196
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:13,070
But that day, seeing him beside you,

197
00:26:13,070 --> 00:26:15,380
I was grateful.

198
00:26:19,230 --> 00:26:23,400
I was thinking you probably felt a bit better because of him.

199
00:26:26,890 --> 00:26:28,580
Yeah.

200
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:31,950
That's why...

201
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,350
   

202
00:26:34,350 --> 00:26:36,840
 I felt comforted. 

203
00:26:49,510 --> 00:26:55,070
   

204
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:01,000
Entering the venue now.

205
00:28:03,150 --> 00:28:05,420
It's the last piece.

