00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:35,790
 On the day before his wedding to Clara,  

210
00:32:35,790 --> 00:32:40,900
 Schumann gifted Clara with a collection of pieces 

211
00:32:40,900 --> 00:32:46,420
 filled with love and happiness. 

212
00:32:46,420 --> 00:32:50,920
 The first song in this collection, "Dedication,"  
     
  (T/N: "Widmung.") 

213
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:57,440
 was later arranged by pianist and composer Liszt  
    

214
00:32:57,440 --> 00:33:01,540
 into a piano piece without lyrics. 

215
00:33:03,610 --> 00:33:09,130
 The person who reached out to me through music  

216
00:33:09,130 --> 00:33:12,360
 before using words 

217
00:33:13,180 --> 00:33:18,750
 was now using wordless music 

218
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:23,720
 to give his heart to me. 

219
00:35:15,540 --> 00:35:18,680
You didn't have to bring all these.

220
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:25,640
I wanted to buy the prettiest flowers in the flower shop, but now that I look at it, they do seem not so great.

221
00:35:26,730 --> 00:35:29,090
No, they're pretty.

222
00:35:34,270 --> 00:35:38,190
Then, go back safely.

223
00:35:38,190 --> 00:35:39,900
Yes, sure.

224
00:35:39,900 --> 00:35:44,170
I'll go with your mother to the bus terminal, so don't worry.

225
00:35:44,170 --> 00:35:45,680
Yes, thank you.

226
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:46,970
Get some rest.

227
00:35:46,970 --> 00:35:49,070
Mother, let's go.

228
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:51,160
Take care.

229
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:57,020
Joon Young.

230
00:36:00,450 --> 00:36:06,370
In the latter part, I teared up.

231
00:36:10,510 --> 00:36:18,450
I don't know anything about the piano, but strangely, I cried.

232
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:24,310
I'll go now.

233
00:36:24,310 --> 00:36:26,350
Take care.

234
00:36:27,330 --> 00:36:29,560
Be happy.

235
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:49,530
   

236
00:37:12,970 --> 00:37:14,950
Yes?

237
00:37:18,390 --> 00:37:22,910
Excuse me, we have to close the venue soon.

238
00:37:23,670 --> 00:37:26,400
I'm sorry, I'll come out right away.

239
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,010
Yes?

240
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:11,810
When did you come?

241
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:18,480
I was a bit late.

242
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:24,580
So I only heard Brahms and "Dedication."

243
00:38:33,770 --> 00:38:39,040
Do you remember when we met at the airport?

244
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:43,990
The performance program tonight

245
00:38:45,580 --> 00:38:52,220
Schumann, Clara, Brahms.

246
00:38:52,910 --> 00:38:56,490
I played it thinking of what you had told me.

247
00:39:00,820 --> 00:39:07,680
Now... I want to play Brahms often.

248
00:39:23,700 --> 00:39:26,880
You asked me before

249
00:39:32,410 --> 00:39:35,600
to be friends, didn't you?

250
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:47,210
I received so much comfort from you.

251
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:51,890
Comfort I received as a friend.

252
00:39:58,670 --> 00:40:07,020
So today, I also came here... as a friend.

253
00:40:13,550 --> 00:40:16,620
But now I think

254
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:24,480
I can't be that kind of friend with you.

255
00:40:36,590 --> 00:40:39,080
I love you.

256
00:41:02,510 --> 00:41:03,860
I love you.

